2025-12-12 | Maximum Sum of a Subarray of Size k

	Question
Given an integer array arr[] and an integer k,  
return the maximum sum of a subarray of size k.

	Approach
1.	Use the **Sliding Window Technique**.
2.	First, compute the sum of the **first k elements**.
	-	This is the initial window sum.
3.	Slide the window one element at a time:
	-	Add the next element entering the window.
	-	Subtract the element leaving the window.
4.	Keep track of the **maximum sum** seen so far.
5.	This avoids recalculating sums repeatedly.
6.	Time Complexity: O(n)  
   Space Complexity: O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int maximumSumSubarray(int k, vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        if (n < k) return 0;

        int windowSum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            windowSum += arr[i];
        }

        int maxSum = windowSum;

        for (int i = k; i < n; i++) {
            windowSum += arr[i] - arr[i - k];
            maxSum = max(maxSum, windowSum);
        }

        return maxSum;
    }
};
